definitions.definition: ( uncountable ) A thick cloud that forms near the ground; the obscurity of such a cloud.
( uncountable ) A mist or film clouding a surface.
( figurative ) A state of mind characterized by lethargy and confusion .
examples: He did so many drugs, he was still in a fog three months after going through detox.

definitions.definition: ( photography ) A silver deposit or other blur on a negative or developed photographic image.

definitions.definition: A new growth of grass appearing on a field that has been mowed or grazed .
Tall and decaying grass left standing after the cutting or grazing season.

main_definition: A new growth of grass appearing on a field that has been mowed or grazed .
